Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) presidential candidate, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar, has said actions are being taken to address the grievances of party members. In a series of tweets yeterday, Atiku said he has a lot of respect for all party members, including governors. “The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) will remain united. Focus on our actions. We are taking action to address the feelings of all party members,” the former Vice President tweeted. “The unity in our community is my priority. Our resolve to unify Nigeria starts in our party and moves to the community, then on to society.   ‘Ekiti, Osun polls litmus test for 2023…     826 Plateau pilgrims set for Saudi Arabia     MSSN holds Ummahaat conference   “Every governor, legislator, and other elected officials produced by our party, and party members and loyalists, are much loved and respected by me. “When they speak, I listen. I do not only listen. Appropriate actions have been taken, are being taken, and will continue to be advanced.” Also, Okowe has assured his party that the misunderstanding over his vice presidential candidacy would resolved soon. Okowa spoke yesterday after a meeting with Vice President Yemi Osinbajo at the State House in Abuja.